## mcp__ardot__create_new_page
Create a new empty page (CANVAS) in a .ardot file.

- Adds a fresh blank page to the current document.
- If `leftPageId` is provided, the new page is inserted **immediately after** that page;
  otherwise it is appended next to the current active page (host default).
- If `name` is provided, the page is renamed to that value after creation.
- By default the editor switches focus to the newly created page (`select: true`).

Returns the newly created `pageId` (use it as `parentId` when later inserting top-level
frames via `batch_edit`).

Parameters:
```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [],
  "properties": {
    "fileId": {
      "description": "Target file ID. If multiple files are open and this is not specified, the tool will return available file IDs to choose from.",
      "type": "string"
    },
    "name": {
      "description": "Optional name for the new page. If omitted, the host editor assigns a default name like \"Page N\".",
      "type": "string"
    },
    "leftPageId": {
      "description": "Optional sibling page ID. The new page will be inserted immediately after this page in the page list.",
      "type": "string"
    },
    "select": {
      "default": true,
      "description": "Whether to switch the editor to the newly created page after creation. Defaults to true.",
      "type": "boolean"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
```

